7.57pm A solid batting performance from Australia, given they've batted twice under lights. Labuschagne, Head shined through and through, while Patterson showed critics that he belongs in Test Cricket. And what about Suranga Lakmal? The old man is showing us he's still got the goods... finishing with 5 for 75, and ensuring that Sri Lanka have a slender hope of drawing/winning the Test. How will Sri Lanka bat with about 20 minutes of cricket left? Let's find out together when we return with the third innings.
